2:T8fa,[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Place","name":"Park Slope","description":"Park Slope is Brooklyn's most beloved family neighborhood — a succession of brownstone-lined streets climbing the western slope of Prospect Park that functions as a small city within the larger boroug","url":"https://withpush.co/neighborhoods/park-slope","geo":{"@type":"GeoCoordinates","latitude":40.6726,"longitude":-73.9777},"address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"Park Slope","addressRegion":"NY","addressCountry":"US"},"containedInPlace":{"@type":"City","name":"New York City"}},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does Push work in Park Slope?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Push connects local creators with merchants in Park Slope, Brooklyn. Creators visit participating businesses, scan a QR code to verify their visit, then publish content. Merchants pay only for verified foot traffic — no guessing required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many campaigns are active in Park Slope right now?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Park Slope currently has 21 active creator campaigns across 27 merchants, with 95 creators operating in this neighborhood."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the average campaign payout in Park Slope?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The average campaign payout in Park Slope is $46 per verified visit. Total verified visits in this neighborhood have reached 2,614."}}]},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"ItemList","name":"Featured Merchants in Park Slope","numberOfItems":3,"itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Olmsted","address":"659 Vanderbilt Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11238","description":"Food & Drink business in Park Slope with 1 active Push campaign."}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Sycamore Bar","address":"1118 Cortelyou Rd, Brooklyn, NY 11218","description":"Nightlife business in Park Slope with 2 active Push campaigns."}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Hungry Ghost Coffee","address":"781 Fulton St, Brooklyn, NY 11217","description":"Coffee business in Park Slope with 2 active Push campaigns."}}]}]4:T43a,Park Slope is Brooklyn's most beloved family neighborhood — a succession of brownstone-lined streets climbing the western slope of Prospect Park that functions as a small city within the larger borough. Fifth Avenue is the commercial spine: a continuous strip of neighborhood restaurants, bars, yoga studios, and specialty shops that sustain a remarkably loyal local customer base. The park itself is Park Slope's primary amenity — weekends bring thousands of residents to its meadows, ball fields, and the Long Meadow. Push campaigns in Park Slope have a distinct character: they're oriented around neighborhood rituals and regulars rather than destination visitors. The brunch campaign genre dominates — Park Slope has one of the highest brunch-table-to-resident ratios in any urban neighborhood in America. Fitness studios, family-friendly dining, and specialty coffee also perform well. The neighborhood's demographics skew toward dual-income households with disposable income and high content-consumption habits, making it an attractive market for premium Push merchants.0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","main",null,{"className":"nh-page","children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"nhd-hero","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container nhd-hero-inner","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"nhd-breadcrumb","aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/","children":"Push"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"nhd-breadcrumb-sep","children":"/"}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/neighborhoods","children":"Neighborhoods"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"nhd-breadc